EVERYONE PLEASE NOTE: If you are getting errors after a successful install such as the following: 

Unable to extract file. 
Extract Error code: 2 

The figure file does not exist. 

DynaZip UnZIP Error: 
ZIP file read error! 

This means that you probably linked to the already extracted iso data on your hard drive. In my experience this does not work and you need to mount the ISO's as a drive.  

A super easy program to mount the ISO's can be found here: http://www.tech-recipes.com/rx/620/xp_small_free_way_to_use_and_mount_images_iso_files_without_burning_them
